<h1>Streamdeck Timer Service</h1>
<h2>How to Use</h2>
<p>This service allows you to configure Streamdeck buttons as timers. Each button can trigger a specific time duration with a custom topic.</p>

<h3>Configure Streamdeck Button</h3>
<ol>
  <li>In Streamdeck, add a "Website" action to your button</li>
  <li>Set the URL format: <code>http://0.0.0.0:9987/timer?time=SECONDS&topic=DESCRIPTION</code></li>
  <li>Example: <code>http://0.0.0.0:9987/timer?time=300&topic=Coffee%20Break</code></li>
</ol>

<h3>API Endpoints</h3>
<ul>
  <li><code>GET /timer?time=30&topic=reading</code> - Start a new timer</li>
  <li><code>GET /timers</code> - View all timers</li>
  <li><code>GET /health</code> - Check service status</li>
</ul>
